article.headline: Penn 88, Dartmouth 62
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. (AP) -- Brian Grandieri made 7 of 9 field goal attempts and scored 15 points as Penn beat Dartmouth for the 23rd straight time, 88-62, Friday night. The Quakers (10-15, 5-3 Ivy League), held without a 3-point basket in a two-point win over the Big Green (8-15, 1-8) three weeks ago, made 6-of-8 long-range baskets while taking a 39-30 lead at the half. They hit four more while opening the second half with a 24-8 run to build their lead to 63-38. They went on to lead by as many as 29. Kevin Egee added 14 points, Andreas Schreiber 12 and Tyler Bernardini 11. Dartmouth, which has lost its last seven games, got 13 points from DeVon Mosley, 12 from Elgin Fitzgerald and 11 from Alex Barnett. The Quakers finished with their largest victory margin of the season and second highest point total.
